<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Seated-Shoulder-Press">Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-seated-shoulder-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell seated</a><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-seated-shoulder-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"> shoulder press</a> is a compound deltoid exercise that targets all three heads of the muscle (anterior, lateral, and posterior). Secondary muscles that support the movement include the triceps, trapezius, and upper pectorals.</p>



<p>This shoulder press helps build overall muscle mass in the shoulders. At the same time, it increases overhead pushing strength. It is a compound exercise that requires the shoulders, chest, and triceps to work together. This makes it an effective functional movement that translates to many daily and sporting actions.</p>



<p>When you do the shoulder press with dumbbells, you force each side of the deltoids to work independently. This prevents the stronger side from taking over. As a result, you are more likely to build even muscle and strength on the left and right sides.</p>



<p>Using dumbbells instead of a barbell allows you to use a variety of grips, including neutral (palms facing). Different hand positions work the shoulders slightly differently.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
