</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Seated Shoulder Press&nbsp;Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Take hold of a pair of dumbbells and sit on a back-supported bench. The back support should be upright.</li>



<li>Bring the dumbbells up to your shoulders. Face your palms forward with elbows bent at 90 degrees. Your back should be completely against the back pad.</li>



<li>Press the dumbbells directly up, stopping just short of full extension.</li>



<li>Lower under control to the start position.</li>



<li>Breathe out as you press the dumbbells up. Breathe out as you lower them.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core tight throughout the movement. This enhances balance and stability.</li>



<li>Your elbows should remain in line with your hips throughout the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your shoulder blades against the back pad at all times.</li>
</ul>



