<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Alternating-Dumbbell-Press">Alternating Dumbbell Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/alternating-dumbbell-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">alternating </a><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/alternating-dumbbell-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell press</a> works all three heads of the deltoid muscle simultaneously. The triceps, upper chest, and core muscles act as secondary muscles to support the movement.</p>



<p>This exercise involves pressing one arm overhead and then alternating with the other arm. This allows you to give total focus and attention to one side of the shoulders at a time. The unilateral nature of this exercise also ensures even strength and muscle development between both sides of the muscle.</p>



<p>This exercise&#8217;s alternating action requires more core stability than other forms of shoulder press. It also helps develop coordination and balance.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
