</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Alternating Dumbbell Press Guide. <span>Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Take hold of a pair of dumbbells and sit on a back-supported bench. Plant your feet firmly on the floor.</li>



<li>Bring the weights up to shoulder level with your elbows bent at 90 degrees.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Press the right-side dumbbell directly overhead, stopping just short of lockout.</li>



<li>Lower the weight to the start position.</li>



<li>Press the left-hand dumbbell to the start position, again stopping just short of lockout.</li>



<li>Continue alternating sides to complete your rep count.</li>



<li>Breathe out as you press the dumbbell up. Breathe in as you lower it.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Do not swing or use momentum to help lift the weight.</li>



<li>Fight against the pull of gravity as you lower the dumbbell.</li>
</ul>



