<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up two pulleys so they are at the bottom positions. Attach two D-shaped handles to the carabiners.</li>



<li>Grasp each handle with your hands facing your legs and bring them between the cable pulleys with your hands by your sides.</li>



<li>Stand in the middle of the cable pulleys with your feet shoulder-width apart. Keep your chest up and head facing forward.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Cross the handles over so they are opposite to each other. Keep your hands by your sides and prepare to lift.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Bring both arms out to your sides until theyâ€™re directly parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position. Bring them back to the starting position under control while exhaling at the same time.</li>



<li>Repeat the same movement pattern for the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure you keep your chest and head up throughout the movement to prevent your back from rounding. This limits lower back stress and injury.</li>



<li>If you donâ€™t have access to D-handles, you can opt out of handles. Grip the ball attachments at the ends of the cables.</li>



<li>Make sure you stand directly in between both cable pulleys. This ensures balanced muscle development between your arms.</li>
</ul>



