<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Behind-The-Neck-Press">Behind The Neck Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/behind-the-neck-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">b</a><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/behind-the-neck-press">ehind-the-neck press</a> is a compound movement that targets the front, lateral, and posterior heads of the deltoids. The posterior head acts mainly to stabilize the shoulder joint. This exercise&#8217;s secondary muscles are the trapezius, triceps, and upper chest.</p>



<p>This exercise works the major upper body muscles, including the chest, shoulders, and triceps. As such, it helps to build overall upper body strength.</p>



<p>Performing the overhead press to the back of the neck increases posterior deltoid involvement. It also reduces pectoral involvement compared to the front press.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
