<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set the J-cups in a power rack at shoulder level. Place an Olympic barbell on the J-cups and load the appropriate weight.</li>



<li>Step under the bar as if setting up for a back squat. Put your hands on the bar slightly wider than shoulder width.</li>



<li>Unrack the bar and take a step back.</li>



<li>Push the bar overhead to a lockout position.</li>



<li>Lower the bar to bring it down behind your head. Stop at mid-head level.</li>



<li>Press back to the start position.</li>



<li>Breathe out as you press the bar up and in as you lower it.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Do not come down lower than mid-head level. This prevents scapular rotation.</li>



<li>Avoid bucking the hips to provide upward momentum.</li>
