<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Arnold-Press">Dumbbell Arnold Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-arnold-press">dumbbell Arnold pres</a><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-arnold-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">s</a> is a dumbbell shoulder press variation. It was a favorite of Arnold Schwarzenegger and was named after him. The key difference compared to the standard press is that you rotate your palms from inward to outward facing.</p>



<p>This exercise works all three heads of the deltoids. The rotational hand movement does a better job than the standard press at activating the posterior head. The secondary muscles that work during the exercise are the triceps, trapezius, and upper chest.</p>



<p>The dumbbell Arnold press builds overall shoulder muscle mass. It also helps improve overall upper body strength, emphasizing the shoulders, triceps, and chest. The unique hand rotation of this exercise improves mobility and flexibility in the shoulder joint.</p>



