<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do&nbsp;</h4>



<ol>
<li>Take hold of a pair of dumbbells and sit on a back-supported bench with your feet firmly planted on the floor. Bring the dumbbells up to shoulder level, palms facing your body.</li>



<li>Press the dumbbells up, twisting your wrists so they face away from your body in the top position.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbells, rotating back to a palms-facing position at the bottom.</li>



<li>Breathe out as you push the weights up and in as you lower them.</li>
</ol>



