<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Barbell-Military-Press">Barbell Military Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-military-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">barbell military press</a> is a compound upper-body exercise that primarily works the shoulders. It emphasizes the front and side delts, with the rear delts mainly acting as a stabilizer.</p>



<p>This exercise increases overall upper body strength and muscle mass. In addition to the shoulders, it improves chest and triceps strength, promoting functional movement.</p>



<p>The barbell military press highly engages the core muscles to provide balance and stability. Thatâ€™s because the exercise is done standing, requiring the core to be more involved than if you were seated.</p>



